        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 6:44PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Babcock State Park, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rainelle and Babcock State Park.

This includes Route 19 between mile markers 27 and 31.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
